Governor of Plateau State, Simon Lalong, has announced restriction of movement in the state ahead of the bye- elections for Bassa/Jos North Federal Constituency and Pankshin South State Constituency. The governor made the announcement in a statement signed by the Commissioner for Information and Communications, Dan Manjang, on Friday night. The two by-elections are scheduled for Saturday, February 26, 2022. The statement read, “In line with the plans by the Independent National Electoral Commission to conduct bye-election for the Jos/Bassa Federal Constituency and the Pankshin South State Constituency on 26th February 2022, the Executive Governor of Plateau State has approved the restriction of movement within the respective constituencies. “Therefore, all vehicular movements will not be allowed in the affected areas from 12:00 Midnight of Friday 25th February 2022 to 6pm of Saturday 26th February 2022. “Only persons on essential duties will be exempted from the restriction. Citizens are advised to adhere to this directive as relevant security agencies have been directed to ensure compliance. “The governor also calls on all eligible voters to come out and exercise their franchise without fear or intimidation as necessary security arrangements have been put in place to ensure that the exercise goes without hitches.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com